@node "1-1" "What You Should Have"
@{b}What You Should Have@{ub}


In the IMANDI Professional package, you should find:

     -This manual

     -The IMANDI Professional Program Disk

     -The Registration card
@endnode

@node "1-2" "The Registration Card"
@next "1-3"
@prev "1-1"
@{b}The Registration Card@{ub}


Please fill out the Registration Card and send it to us.  This will allow us
to notify you when there are updates and new versions of IMANDI Professional
available.
@endnode

@node "1-3" "IMANDI Professional System Requirements"
@next "1-4"
@prev "1-2"
@{b}IMANDI Professional System Requirements@{ub}


IMANDI Professional will work on any Amiga computer with at least 1.5
megabytes of RAM and Amiga OS 2.04 or higher.  An accelerated system will
greatly enhance performance.  A hard drive is recommended, but not required.
@endnode

@node "1-4" "Backup Copies"
@next "1-5"
@prev "1-3"
@{b}Backup Copies@{ub}


Before you use IMANDI Professional, it is a good idea to make a backup copy
of the original disk.  Use this copy, and keep the original in a safe place.
@endnode

@node "1-5" "Invoice Forms"
@next "1-6"
@prev "1-4"
@{b}Invoice Forms@{ub}


One copy of each of the three varieties of invoice forms is included in the
IMANDI Professional package, as well as PageStream files for the
corresponding invoice forms.  It is recommended that the original copies of
these invoice forms be kept in a safe place where they will not be lost or
damaged.  Use copies of these invoice forms, or have a printing service
print copies for you.  Individual replacements for the invoice forms are
available from Egad International at a reasonable price.  Contact Egad
International for more information.
@endnode

@node "1-6" "Installation"
@next "1-7"
@prev "1-5"
@{b}Installation@{ub}


@{b}Hard Drive Users:@{ub}

Run the IMANDI Professional HD_Install program.  You need at least 1/2 of a
megabyte of hard drive space free.

Follow the installation program's instructions.


@{b}Floppy Users:@{ub}

Rename your copy of the IMANDI program disk to "IMANDI_Pro" with no spaces.

The IMANDI Professional disk is not bootable.  The following assigns are
suggested, but not required:

    Assign Customers: IMANDI_Pro:Customers
    Assign Inventory: IMANDI_Pro:Inventory
    Assign Invoice_Forms: IMANDI_Pro:Invoice_Forms


@{i}Please view the readme file on the IMANDI Professional Program disk for
changes, modifications, and other information.@{ui}
@endnode

@node "1-7" "Starting IMANDI Professional"
@prev "1-6"
@{b}Starting IMANDI Professional@{ub}


Double-click on the IMANDI Professional icon to start IMANDI Professional.
After a moment, IMANDI Professional will be  ready to use.  If there were no
major problems during startup, there will be an "IMANDI Professional 1.0 is
now online" message at the bottom of the main screen in the status bar.
@endnode

@node "2-0" "The Main Control Panel"
The Main Control Panel


The main control panel of IMANDI Professional is where all of the editors
are started from.  On the main control panel, there are seven buttons: @{b}New,
Open, Customer, Inventory, Prefs, Print, and Quit.@{ub}  The following chapters
will describe each of these in detail.
@endnode

@node "3-0" "The Customer Editor"
@next "3-1"
@{b}The Customer Editor@{ub}


The @{i}Customer Editor@{ui} is the portion of IMANDI Professional that allows for
the entry of customers.  Once a customer file has been created, invoices can
be entered for that customer.  

The @{i}Customer Editor@{ui} can be accessed by clicking on the @{b}Customer Editor
Button@{ub} on the main panel or by pressing@{b} F3@{ub} on the keyboard.  The Customer
Editor screen can be shrunk or expanded by using @{b}F9@{ub} and @{b}F10@{ub}, respectively.
@endnode

@node "3-1" "The Customer Editor Menus"
@next "3-2"
@prev "3-0"
@{b}The Customer Editor Menus@{ub}


The following are descriptions of menu functions available from the Customer
menu.

@{b}@{i}New                                    <Amiga N>@{ub}@{ui}

Erases the current customer on the screen, allowing a new customer to be
entered.  Be sure to save the current customer before using this function.

@{b}@{i}Open...                                <Amiga O>@{ub}@{ui}

Brings up a file open requester allowing a previously saved file to be
opened for viewing or editing.

@{b}@{i}Save                                   <Amiga V>@{ub}@{ui}

Saves changes to the customer currently open.

@{b}@{i}Save As...                             <Amiga S>@{ub}@{ui}

Brings up a file save requester allowing the current customer to be saved to
disk.

@{b}@{i}Print...                               <Amiga P>@{ub}@{ui}

Opens the Customer Print Requester.

@{b}The Customer Print Requester@{ub}

The @{i}Customer Print Requester@{ui} allows the selection of formfeeds and the
option to clear the discount information of the customers to be printed.

@{b}@{i}Print@{ub}@{ui}

Opens a requester allowing one or more customers to be printed.  To print
more than one customer, hold down the Shift key and click on the desired
customers.

@{b}@{i}Form Feed@{ub}@{ui}

Adds form feeds when printing to the @{b}PRT:@{ub} device (Printer).  Three customers
will be printed per page, then a form feed.

@{b}@{i}Clear Discount Info@{ub}@{ui}

Sets the List @{b}Total, Earned Discount, and Lost Discount@{ub} fields of the
printed customers to 0.00.

@{b}@{i}Cancel@{ub}@{ui}

Closes the Print Requester.
@endnode

@node "3-2" "The Customer Editor Information Fields"
@next "3-3"
@prev "3-1"
@{b}The Customer Editor Information Fields@{ub}

The following are descriptions of the information fields in the Customer
Editor.

@{b}@{i}Sold To - Line 1@{ub}@{ui}

This field contains the first line of the @{b}Sold To@{ub} portion of the customer
file that will be printed in the @{b}Sold To@{ub} area on the invoice.

@{b}@{i}Sold To - Line 2@{ub}@{ui}

This field contains the second line of the @{b}Sold To@{ub} portion of the customer
file that will be printed in the @{b}Sold To@{ub} area on the invoice.

@{b}@{i}Sold To - Line 3@{ub}@{ui}

This field contains the third line of the @{b}Sold To@{ub} portion of the customer
file that will be printed in the @{b}Sold To@{ub} area on the invoice.

@{b}@{i}Sold To - Line 4@{ub}@{ui}

This field contains the fourth line of the @{b}Sold To@{ub} portion of the customer
file that will be printed in the @{b}Sold To@{ub} area on the invoice.

@{b}@{i}Ship To - Line 1@{ub}@{ui}

This field contains the first line of the @{b}Ship To@{ub} portion of the customer
file that will be printed in the @{b}Sold To@{ub} area on the invoice.

@{b}@{i}Ship To - Line 2@{ub}@{ui}

This field contains the second line of the @{b}Ship To@{ub} portion of the customer
file that will be printed in the @{b}Sold To@{ub} area on the invoice.

@{b}@{i}Ship To - Line 3@{ub}@{ui}

This field contains the third line of the@{b} Ship To@{ub} portion of the customer
file that will be printed in the @{b}Sold To@{ub} area on the invoice.

@{b}@{i}Ship To - Line 4@{ub}@{ui}

This field contains the fourth line of the @{b}Ship To@{ub} portion of the customer
file that will be printed in the @{b}Sold To@{ub} area on the invoice.

The arrow buttons to the right of the @{b}Ship To@{ub} fields will copy the
information contained in the corresponding @{b}Sold To@{ub} fields on the  left.

@{b}@{i}YTD List Total@{ub}@{ui}

This field contains the year to date total purchases of the customer before
discounts, taxes, shipping, etc.  Leave this field blank when entering a new
customer.  IMANDI Professional will keep an accumulating total that can be
automatically cleared when the customer is printed.

@{b}@{i}YTD Earned Discount@{ub}@{ui}

This field contains the year to date earned discounts of the customer. Leave
this field blank when entering a new customer. IMANDI Professional will keep
an accumulating   total that can be automatically cleared when the customer
is printed.

@{b}@{i}YTD Lost Discount@{ub}@{ui}

This field contains the year to date lost discounts of the customer. Leave
this field blank when entering a new customer.  IMANDI Professional will
keep an accumulating total that can be automatically cleared when the
customer is printed.

@{b}@{i}Contact@{ub}@{ui}

This field contains the contact's name.

@{b}@{i}Phone #@{ub}@{ui}

This field contains the customer's phone number.  If there is  more than one
number, put the alternate numbers in the @{b}Other Customer Info@{ub}" link "3-4" 0}
area.

@{b}@{i}FAX #@{ub}@{ui}

This field contains the customer's FAX number.  If there is more than one
FAX number, put the alternate numbers in the @{b}Other Customer Info@{ub}" link "3-4"
0} area.

@{b}@{i}Parts Tax Rate@{ub}@{ui}

This field contains the parts tax rate.  You must enter the tax rate as a
decimal for percentages (ie: .06 for 6% tax. 6 would be 600% tax).

@{b}@{i}Labor Tax Rate@{ub}@{ui}

This field contains the labor tax rate.  You must enter the tax rate as a
decimal for percentages (ie: .06 for 6% tax. 6 would be 600% tax).

@{b}@{i}Travel Tax Rate@{ub}@{ui}

This field contains the travel tax rate.  You must enter the tax rate as a
decimal for percentages (ie: .06 for 6% tax. 6 would be 600% tax).

@{b}@{i}Mileage Tax Rate@{ub}@{ui}

This field contains the mileage tax rate.  You must enter the tax rate as a
decimal for percentages (ie: .06 for 6% tax. 6 would be 600% tax).
@endnode

@node "3-3" "The Discount Type Buttons"
@next "3-4"
@prev "3-2"
@{b}The Discount Type Buttons@{ub}

There are several types of customers that can be set in IMANDI Professional.
A customer can be any one of the five types listed below.  Each has a
different item discount rate associated with it.  The discount rates can be
set in the Preferences Editor.

@{b}@{i}Blanket@{ub}@{ui}

This button will set the customer to the Blanket discount rate that is set
in the @{i}Preferences Editor@{ui}.  The default discount is 10%. This is usually
used for your best customers, or ones that have a full service contract or
similar status.

@{b}@{i}As Needed@{ub}@{ui}

This button will set the customer to the As Needed discount rate that is set
in the @{i}Preferences Editor@{ui}.  The default discount is 5%. This is usually used
for your less active customers, who may have a lesser service contract, or
lesser status than a Blanket customer.

@{b}@{i}Non-User@{ub}@{ui}

This button will set the customer to the Non-User discount rate that is set
in the @{i}Preferences Editor@{ui}.  The discount is 0%.  This is usually used for
your customers who do not have a service contract, or do not have a
preferred customer status.

@{b}@{i}NLD As Needed@{ub}@{ui}

This button will set the customer to the As Needed discount rate that is set
in the @{i}Preferences Editor@{ui}.  This customer will get a discount, but it will
not be recorded in the @{b}YTD Earned Discount @{ub}and@{b} YTD Lost Discount@{ub} fields.

@{b}@{i}NLD Non-User@{ub}@{ui}

This button will set the customer to the Non-User discount rate that is set
in the @{i}Preferences Editor@{ui}.  This customer will not get a discount, and it
will not be recorded in the @{b}YTD Earned Discount@{ub} and@{b} YTD Lost Discount@{ub}
fields.
@endnode

@node "3-4" "The Other Customer Info Area"
@prev "3-3"
@{b}The Other Customer Info Area@{ub}


Any extra information can be stored in the Other Customer Info area: Notes,
alternate phone and FAX numbers, BBS numbers, etc.  There is no size limit
on this area.
@endnode

@node "4-0" "The Inventory Editor"
@next "4-1"
@{b}The Inventory Editor@{ub}


The @{i}Inventory Editor@{ui} is the part of IMANDI Professional that manages the
inventory databases.  The inventory databases store information about
different items such as:  part names, descriptions, quantities, prices,
suppliers, and weights.  There is no limit on the size or number of
databases.

The Inventory Editor can be accessed by clicking on the @{b}Inventory Editor
Button@{ub} on the main panel or by pressing@{b} F4@{ub} on the keyboard.
@endnode

@node "4-1" "The Inventory Editor Menus"
@next "4-2"
@prev "4-0"
@{b}The Inventory Editor Menus@{ub}

The following are descriptions of menu functions available from the
@{b}Inventory @{ub}menu.

@{b}@{i}New Database                         <Amiga N>@{ub}@{ui}

Clears the current database from memory, and starts a new one.  Make sure
the current database has been saved before using this function.

@{b}@{i}Open...                                <Amiga O>@{ub}@{ui}

Brings up a file open requester allowing a previously saved database to be
opened for viewing or editing.

@{b}@{i}Save                                   <Amiga V>@{ub}@{ui}

Saves changes to the currently open database.

@{b}@{i}Save As...                             <Amiga S>@{ub}@{ui}

Brings up a file save requester allowing the current database to be saved to
disk.

The following are descriptions of the menu options available from the
@{b}Reports@{ub} menu.

@{b}@{i}Inventory Report                       <Amiga I>@{ub}@{ui}

Generates a report from the database currently open.  This report includes
all information contained within the fields on the @{i}Inventory Editor@{ui} window,
with exception to the sales record document.  A print requester will be
opened, allowing the selection of print parameters.

@{b}@{i}Page Report                            <Amiga P>@{ub}@{ui}

Generates a report from the current item displayed.  This report includes
all information contained within the fields on the @{i}Inventory Editor@{ui} window,
including to the sales record document.  A print requester will be opened,
allowing the selection of print parameters.

@{b}@{i}Value Report                           <Amiga L>@{ub}@{ui}

Generates a report from the database currently open.  This report includes:
Item Name, Quantity, Quantity Sold, Cost, Price In Stock Value, and Sold
Values, as well as Total In Stock Values for the entire database.  A print
requester will be opened, allowing the selection of form feeds and the print
destination.

@{b}@{i}Clear Sold                             <Amiga C>@{ub}@{ui}

Sets all @{b}Sold@{ub} fields in the current database to 0.
@endnode

@node "4-2" "The Inventory Editor Information Fields"
@next "4-3"
@prev "4-1"
@{b}The Inventory Editor Information Fields@{ub}


The following are descriptions of the information fields in the @{i}Invoice
Editor@{ui}.

@{b}@{i}Part Name@{ub}@{ui}

This field contains the name of the item.

@{b}@{i}Description - Line 1@{ub}@{ui}

This field contains the first line of description.

@{b}@{i}Description - Line 2@{ub}@{ui}

This field contains the second line of description.

@{b}@{i}Description - Line 3@{ub}@{ui}

This field contains the third line of description.

@{b}@{i}Quantity@{ub}@{ui}

This field contains the current quantity of the item in stock.

@{b}@{i}Recommended Quantity@{ub}@{ui}

This field contains the recommended quantity of the item to have in stock.

@{b}@{i}Quantity Sold@{ub}@{ui}

This field contains the number of items sold.

@{b}@{i}Quantity Description@{ub}@{ui}

This field contains the description of the quantity (ie. each, set, box).

@{b}@{i}Cost@{ub}@{ui}

This field contains the cost of the item.

@{b}@{i}Price@{ub}@{ui}

This field contains the price of the item.

@{b}@{i}Supplier@{ub}@{ui}

This field contains the name of the supplier of the item.

@{b}@{i}Weight@{ub}@{ui}

This field contains the weight of the item.

@{b}@{i}Discount?@{ub}@{ui}

This field contains either "y" for yes, if it is discountable, or "n" for
no, if the item is not discountable.

@{b}@{i}Taxable?@{ub}@{ui}

This field contains either "y" for yes, if it is taxable, or "n" for no, if
the item is not taxable.
@endnode

@node "4-3" "The Inventory Editor Utility Fields"
@next "4-4"
@prev "4-2"
@{b}The Inventory Editor Utility Fields@{ub}


The following is a description of the utility field in the @{i}Inventory Editor@{ui}.
This field produces an immediate action.

@{b}@{i}Search for Part@{ub}@{ui}

Enter an item name to search for, and the closest match to the name that you
enter will be found.
@endnode

@node "4-4" "The Inventory Editor Buttons"
@next "4-5"
@prev "4-3"
@{b}The Inventory Editor Buttons@{ub}


@{b}@{i}Left Arrow@{ub}@{ui}

Displays the previous database item.

@{b}@{i}Right Arrow@{ub}@{ui}

Displays the next database item.

@{b}@{i}Add@{ub}@{ui}

Adds a new item to the current database.  The Part Name field will be
automatically selected.  Begin entering the appropriate information there.
After the third description line has been entered, the Restock Editor will
open.  See @{"The Restock Editor" link "4-5" 0} for more information about the Restock
Editor.

@{b}@{i}Delete@{ub}@{ui}

Deletes the displayed item in the current database.

@{b}@{i}Restock@{ub}@{ui}

Opens the @{b}Restock Editor@{ub}.  See Section @{"The Restock Editor" link "4-5" 0} for more
information.
@endnode

@node "4-5" "The Restock Editor"
@next "4-6"
@prev "4-4"
@{b}The Restock Editor@{ub}


The @{b}Restock Editor@{ub} is used when entering a new item, replenishing an
existing item, or removing a number of items from a database.

@{b}@{i}Date of Change@{ub}@{ui}

This field contains the date when the change to the item's quantity took
place.  This field's default is the current day if your Amiga has a clock.

@{b}@{i}Purchase Order@{ub}@{ui}

This field contains the purchase order number, if any.

@{b}@{i}Description@{ub}@{ui}

This field contains the action description.  If you are adding to the item's
quantity, use the description of "Restock" or something similar.  "Restock"
is default.  If you are taking away from an item's quantity, an appropriate
description might be "Reduction."

@{b}@{i}Quantity Change@{ub}@{ui}

This field contains the quantity change.  For example if you are adding 10
to the item, put in 10.  If you are removing 10, then put in -10.
@endnode

@node "4-6" "The Inventory Editor Document"
@prev "4-5"
@{b}The Inventory Editor Document@{ub}


The @{b}Inventory Editor Document@{ub} contains all modifications to the item.  The
information recorded is the Quantity, Purchase Order #, Action Description,
Quantity Change, and the Date of Change.
@endnode

@node "5-0" "The Preferences Editor"
@next "5-1"
@{b}The Preferences Editor@{ub}


The @{i}Preferences Editor@{ui} allows the modification of most global values that
are used throughout IMANDI Professional.

The Preferences Editor can be accessed by clicking on the @{b}Preferences Editor
Button@{ub} on the main panel or by pressing @{b}F5@{ub} on the keyboard.
@endnode

@node "5-1" "The Preferences Editor Information Fields"
@next "5-2"
@prev "5-0"
@{b}The Preferences Editor Information Fields@{ub}


The following are descriptions of the information fields in the @{i}Preferences
Editor@{ui}.

@{b}@{i}IYP Labor@{ub}@{ui}

This field contains the In Your Plant Labor rate.  This is the price charged
for services performed at your customer's location.

@{b}@{i}AOP Labor@{ub}@{ui}

This field contains the At Our Plant Labor rate.  The is the price charged
price charged for services performed at your location.

@{b}@{i}Mileage@{ub}@{ui}

This field contains the rate charged per mile of driving to the customer's
location.

@{b}@{i}Travel@{ub}@{ui}

This field contains the rate charged for the time traveling to the
customer's location to provide service work.

@{b}@{i}Parts Tax Rate@{ub}@{ui}

This field contains the default parts tax rate.  You must enter the tax rate
as a decimal for percentages (ie: .06 for 6% tax. 6 would be 600% tax).

@{b}Labor Tax Rate@{ub}

This field contains the default labor tax rate.  You must enter the tax rate
as a decimal for percentages (ie: .06 for 6% tax. 6 would be 600% tax).

@{b}@{i}Travel Tax Rate@{ub}@{ui}

This field contains the default travel tax rate.  You must enter the tax
rate as a decimal for percentages (ie: .06 for 6% tax. 6 would be 600%
tax).

@{b}@{i}Mileage Tax Rate@{ub}@{ui}

This field contains the default mileage tax rate.  You must enter the tax
rate as a decimal for percentages (ie: .06 for 6% tax.  6 would be 600%
tax).

@{b}@{i}Blanket Discount - In Your Plant Labor@{ub}@{ui}

This field contains the default Blanket customer discount for services
performed at the customer's location.

@{b}@{i}As Needed Discount - In Your Plant Labor@{ub}@{ui}

This field contains the default As Needed customer discount for services
performed at the customer's location.

@{b}@{i}Blanket Discount - At Our Plant Labor@{ub}@{ui}

This field contains the default Blanket customer discount for services
performed at your location.

@{b}@{i}As Needed Discount - At Our Plant Labor@{ub}@{ui}

This field contains the default As Needed customer discount for services
performed at your location.

@{b}@{i}Blanket Discount - Parts@{ub}@{ui}

This field contains the default Blanket customer discount on items in the
inventory database. This value must be a percentage (ie. .10 for 10%).

@{b}@{i}As Needed Discount - Parts@{ub}@{ui}

This field contains the default As Needed customer discount on items in the
inventory database.  This value must be a percentage (ie. .10 for 10%).

@{b}@{i}Blanket Discount - Mileage@{ub}@{ui}

This field contains the default Blanket customer discount on mileage. This
value must be a percentage (ie. .10 for 10%).

@{b}@{i}As Needed Discount - Mileage@{ub}@{ui}

This field contains the default As Needed customer discount on mileage. This
value must be a percentage (ie. .10 for 10%).

@{b}@{i}Blanket Discount - Travel Time@{ub}@{ui}

This field contains the default Blanket customer discount on travel time.
This value must be a percentage (ie. .10 for 10%).

@{b}@{i}As Needed Discount - Travel Time@{ub}@{ui}

This field contains the default As Needed customer discount on travel time.
This value must be a percentage (ie. .10 for 10%).

@{b}@{i}Header Info - Invoice #@{ub}@{ui}

This field contains the current invoice number.

@{b}@{i}Header Info - FOB@{ub}@{ui}

This field contains the shipping point.

@{b}@{i}Header Info - Terms@{ub}@{ui}

This field contains the terms of the invoice (ie. Net/25).
@endnode

@node "5-2" "The Preferences Editor Buttons"
@next "5-3"
@prev "5-1"
@{b}The Preferences Editor Buttons@{ub}


@{b}@{i}Basic Bottom@{ub}@{ui}

This option will set the default invoice printing type to basic bottom.
Basic bottom means that the discounting information and list totals will not
be printed on the invoice.

@{b}@{i}No Bottom@{ub}@{ui}

This option sets the default invoice printing type to be the same as a
normal bottom, but without the earned and lost discount information.

@{b}@{i}Shipping Tax@{ub}@{ui}

This option turns shipping taxation on.  All shipping charges will be
taxed.

@{b}@{i}Customer Save@{ub}@{ui}

This option will set customer saving as default.  When an invoice is closed,
a file save requester will automatically open to save the customer changes.
This option is highly recommended for keeping track of sales and customer
discounts.

@{b}@{i}Database Save@{ub}@{ui}

This option will set database saving as default.  When an invoice is closed,
a file save requester will automatically open to save the inventory
database.  This option is also highly recommended to keep track of the
inventory levels.

@{b}@{i}Invoice Save@{ub}@{ui}

This option will set invoice form saving as default.  When an invoice is
closed, a file save requester will automatically open to save the invoice
items as a file that can be opened for reference at a later time.
@endnode

@node "5-3" "The Shipper List"
@prev "5-2"
@{b}The Shipper List@{ub}

The @{b}Shipper List@{ub} is a document at the bottom of the @{i}Preferences Editor@{ui}
window that contains the list of shippers.  This list is unlimited, and can
contain whatever shippers desired.
@endnode

@node "6-0" "The Header Editor"
@next "6-1"
@{b}The Header Editor@{ub}

The @{i}Header Editor@{ui} allows general invoice information to be entered:  the
Invoice Number, Salesperson, Date, P.O. Number, Part Number, Date Shipped,
Shipper, FOB, and Terms.  Since this editor is only accessed when using the
New Invoice Function, you may want to skip this section of the manual until
you have read about the @{"New Invoice Function" link "Sub_8" 0}.
@endnode

@node "6-1" "The Header Editor Information Fields"
@prev "6-0"
@{b}@{i}The Header Editor Information Fields

@{ub}@{ui}
The following are descriptions of the information fields in the @{i}Header
Editor@{ui}.

@{b}@{i}Invoice #@{ub}@{ui}

This field contains the invoice number that will be used for the new
invoice.

@{b}@{i}Salesperson@{ub}@{ui}

This field contains the name or initials of the sales representative, if
any, for the customer that the invoice is being made for.

@{b}@{i}Date@{ub}@{ui}

This field contains the date that the invoice is being created on.  This
field is automatically filled with the current date if your Amiga has a
clock.

@{b}@{i}P.O. Number@{ub}@{ui}

This field contains the customer's purchase order number, if any.

@{b}@{i}Part Number@{ub}@{ui}

This field contains the part number if the invoice is being created with
only one item in the body.

@{b}@{i}Date Shipped@{ub}@{ui}

This field contains the date that the items on the invoice will be shipped.
This field is automatically filled with the same date in the@{b} Date@{ub} field.

@{b}@{i}Shipped VIA@{ub}@{ui}

This field will automatically open a requester in which you can double click
on the desired shipper from a list that has been set in the @{"Preferences" link "Sub_5" 0}
@{"Editor" link "Sub_5" 0}.  The arrow to the right of this field will re-open the requester if
you wish to change your selection.

@{b}@{i}FOB@{ub}@{ui}

This field contains the shipping point for the order.

@{b}@{i}Terms@{ub}@{ui}

This field contains the terms of the invoice (ie. Net/25).
@endnode

@node "7-0" "The Invoice Editor"
@next "7-1"
@{b}The Invoice Editor@{ub}


The @{i}Invoice Editor@{ui} is the heart of IMANDI Professional.  This is where the
body of the invoice is created and where the invoice is generated.  Since
this editor can only be accessed through the @{b}New Invoice Function@{ub}, you may
want to skip this chapter for now and go on to the section about the @{"New" link "Sub_8" 0}
@{"Invoice Function" link "Sub_8" 0}.
@endnode

@node "7-1" "The Invoice Editor Mode Menu"
@prev "7-0"
@{b}The Invoice Editor Mode Menu@{ub}


To use the @{i}Invoice Editor@{ui}, it must be put into one of six modes:  Parts,
Labor, Travel Time, Miles, Pass Thru, or Babble.  Each mode will cause the
@{i}Invoice Editor@{ui} to behave differently.  The default mode is Parts mode.



@{b}@{i}Parts                                <Amiga 1>@{ub}@{ui}

This menu option puts the @{i}Invoice Editor@{ui} into Parts Mode.  When Parts Mode
is activated, any part name entered into the @{b}Part Name@{ub} field will be
searched for in the database currently open in the @{i}Inventory Editor@{ui}.

@{b}@{i}Labor                                <Amiga 2>@{ub}@{ui}

This menu option puts the @{i}Invoice Editor@{ui} into Labor Mode.  When Labor Mode
is activated, you have the option of pressing either the @{b}At Our Plant@{ub} button
or @{b}In Your Plant@{ub} button.

@{b}@{i}Travel Time                          <Amiga 3>@{ub}@{ui}

This menu option puts the @{i}Invoice Editor@{ui} into Travel Time Mode, allowing the
entry of a travel time item.

@{b}@{i}Miles                                <Amiga 4>@{ub}@{ui}

This menu option puts the @{i}Invoice Editor@{ui} into Miles Mode, allowing the entry
of a mileage item.

@{b}@{i}Pass-Thru                            <Amiga 5>@{ub}@{ui}

This menu option puts the @{i}Invoice Editor@{ui} into Pass-Thru Mode allowing the
entry of any undefined item.

@{b}@{i}Babble                               <Amiga 6>@{ub}@{ui}

This menu option puts the @{i}Invoice Editor@{ui} into Babble Mode allowing for the
entry of single lines of text in the body of the invoice.
@endnode

@node "7-2" "The Invoice Editor Action and Information Fields"
@next "7-3"
@prev "7-1"
@{b}The Invoice Editor Action and Information Fields@{ub}


The following are descriptions of the utility and information fields in the
@{i}Invoice Editor@{ui}.

@{b}@{i}Part Name@{ub}@{ui}

This field allows the entry of an item name, which will be searched for in
the currently open inventory database.  If found, the information will be
automatically entered into the fields in the @{i}Invoice Editor@{ui}.

@{b}@{i}Description 1@{ub}@{ui}

This field allows the entry of one line of description that will be printed
below the information in the @{b}Part Name@{ub} field.

@{b}@{i}Description 2@{ub}@{ui}

This field allows the entry of one line of description that will be printed
below the information in the @{b}Description 1@{ub} field.

@{b}@{i}Description 3@{ub}@{ui}

This field allows the entry of one line of description that will be printed
below the information in the @{b}Description 2@{ub} field.

@{b}@{i}Quantity@{ub}@{ui}

This field allows the entry of the current quantity of the current item.

@{b}@{i}Quantity Description@{ub}@{ui}

This field allows the entry of the description of the quantity (ie. each,
set, box).

@{b}@{i}Unit Price@{ub}@{ui}

This field allows the entry of the unit price for the current item.

@{b}@{i}Amount@{ub}@{ui}

This field allows the entry of the amount price for the current item.

@{b}@{i}Discount %@{ub}@{ui}

This field allows the entry of a percentage discount on the current item.
The percentage must be in decimal form.@{b}@{i}

Discount $@{ub}@{ui}

This field allows the entry of a monetary discount on the current item.

@{b}@{i}Tax Rate %@{ub}@{ui}

This field contains the tax rate for the current item. This percentage must
be in decimal form.
@endnode

@node "7-3" "The Invoice Editor Buttons"
@prev "7-2"
@{b}The Invoice Editor Buttons@{ub}


@{b}@{i}Item -@{ub}@{ui}

This button decreases the item number by one.

@{b}@{i}Item +@{ub}@{ui}

This button increases the item number by one.

@{b}@{i}Search@{ub}@{ui}

This button, when checked, allows for database searching when in Parts Mode.
@endnode

@node "8-0" "The New Invoice Button"
@next "8-1"
@{b}The New Invoice Function@{ub}


The @{b}New Invoice Button@{ub} starts a new invoice.  IMANDI Pro will open the
@{"Customer Editor" link "Sub_3" 0}, the @{"Header Editor" link "Sub_6" 0}, the @{"Invoice Editor" link "Sub_7" 0}, and the @{"Inventory" link "Sub_4" 0}
@{"Editor" link "Sub_4" 0} -- all at the same time.  Each of these will be utilized in the
creation of a new invoice.
@endnode

@node "8-1" "Creating a New Invoice"
@prev "8-0"
@{b}@{i}Creating a New invoice@{ub}@{ui}


@{b}Step 1@{ub}

Press the @{b}New Invoice@{ub} button on the main panel and wait for all four editors
to open.  The @{i}Customer Editor@{ui} window and the @{i}Header Editor@{ui} window will
appear in front of the other editors.

@{b}Step 2@{ub}

Click in the @{i}Customer Editor@{ui} window.  If the desired customer is already
saved to disk, select @{b}Open@{ub} from the menu and load that customer. If the
customer does not exist on disk, select @{b}New@{ub} from the menu, and proceed to
fill in the fields appropriately.  When either is completed, press @{b}F9@{ub} to
shrink the window, click on the window back button, and go on to Step 3.  If
you are unsure about any function in the @{i}Customer Editor@{ui}, refer to the
section on the @{"Customer Editor" link "Sub_3" 0}.

@{b}Step 3@{ub}

Click in the @{b}Invoice #@{ub} field in the @{i}Header Editor@{ui}.  Fill in each field
appropriately.  When done, send the @{i}Header Editor@{ui} to the back of the screen
by pressing the window back button.  If you are unsure about any function in
the @{i}Header Editor@{ui}, refer to the section on the @{"Header Editor" link "Sub_6" 0}.

@{b}Step 4@{ub}

If you will be utilizing an inventory database for the invoice, click in the
@{i}Inventory Editor@{ui} and open an existing inventory database by selecting @{b}Open@{ub}
from the menu or create a new database by adding items to the currently
empty inventory database.  Once this is completed, click in the @{i}Invoice
Editor@{ui} window.  If you are not using an inventory database for the invoice,
click in the @{i}Invoice Editor@{ui} window.

@{b}Step 5@{ub}

Select the desired mode from the menu, and enter in the appropriate
information.  If you are unsure about any function in the Invoice Editor,
refer to the section on the @{"Invoice Editor" link "Sub_7" 0}.  When you are finished entering
items, go on to Step 6.

@{b}Step 6@{ub}

To print the invoice, click on @{b}Print@{ub} in the main panel. The invoice may be
modified even after it has been printed.  For more information about the
@{b}Print@{ub} function refer to the section on the @{"Print Function" link "Sub_9" 0}.

@{b}Step 7@{ub}

When the invoice has been completed and printed, click on the @{i}Invoice
Editor@{ui}'s close buttons.  This will shut down the current invoice and return
you to the main panel shutting down all editors.  If your preferences are
set to customer, inventory, or invoice form saving, save requesters will
open requesting save file names.  When everything is saved, the editors will
close.  If you do not wish to save the files, select cancel on the save
requesters.
@endnode

@node "9-0" "The Print Requester"
@next "9-1"
@{b}The Print Function@{ub}


The @{b}Print Function@{ub} is only available when a new invoice is open.  Click on
the @{b}Print@{ub} button when finished entering items in the @{i}Invoice Editor@{ui} to open
the @{b}Invoice Print Requester@{ub}.  In this requester, the shipping charges, type
of invoice, formfeeds, and print destination are set.

The Print Requester can be opened by clicking on the @{b}Print@{ub} Button on the
main panel or by pressing@{b} F6@{ub} on the keyboard.
@endnode

@node "9-1" "The Print Requester Fields"
@next "9-2"
@prev "9-0"
@{b}The Print Requester Fields@{ub}


@{b}@{i}Shipping@{ub}@{ui}

This field contains the amount to be charged for shipping.

@{b}@{i}Print Destination@{ub}@{ui}

This field contains the print destination. @{b} PRT:@{ub} will print to the printer.
File save paths may also be entered, or can be chosen by clicking on the
arrow button to the right of the @{b}Print Destination@{ub} field.
@endnode

@node "9-2" "The Print Requester Buttons"
@prev "9-1"
@{b}The Print Requester's Buttons@{ub}


@{b}@{i}Basic Bottom@{ub}@{ui}

This option will set the default invoice printing type to basic bottom.
Basic bottom means that the discounting information and list totals will not
be printed on the invoice.

@{b}@{i}No Discount Print@{ub}@{ui}

This option will set the default invoice printing type to be the same as a
normal bottom, but without the earned and lost discount information.

@{b}@{i}Shipping Tax@{ub}@{ui}

This option will enable shipping taxation.

@{b}@{i}Formfeed@{ub}@{ui}

This option will enable form feeds at the end of each page.
@endnode

@node "10-0" "The Open Function"
@{b}The Open Function@{ub}


The @{b}Open@{ub} function does the same thing as the @{b}New@{ub} function.  The only
difference is that it will open a saved invoice and insert the contents of
that invoice into the items of a new invoice.  This means that it will start
a new invoice, and put the items of the old invoice into the items of the
new invoice in the @{i}Invoice Editor@{ui}" link "Sub_7" 0}.
@endnode

@node "11-0" "The Quit Function"
@{b}The Quit Function@{ub}


Pressing the @{b}Quit@{ub} button on the main panel will quit IMANDI Professional.
@endnode

@node "12-0" "Tutorial Explanation"
@next "12-1"
@{b}Tutorial Explanation@{ub}


This tutorial is designed to familiarize you with the operations of IMANDI
Professional.  While it does not utilize every feature available, this
tutorial gives you a feel of how most things in IMANDI Professional work.
Follow the tutorial exactly the first time through, and later explore and
try other features detailed in  the reference section of this manual.  The
tutorial assumes that you have already installed and have just started
IMANDI Professional.
@endnode

@node "12-1" "Tutorial"
@prev "12-0"
@{b}Tutorial@{ub}


@{b}Step 1@{ub}

First, we will create a new customer for use in IMANDI Professional.  For
any invoice to be created, there must be a customer file.  Click on the
@{b}Customer Editor@{ub} button.  The @{i}Customer Editor@{ui} will now open its window. Click
in the field labeled @{b}Sold To Line 1@{ub}.  Enter "Test Customer" into this field.
Press return.  Enter "123 Somewhere Street" and press return.  Enter
"Someplace, CT  06066" and press return.  Enter "USA" and press return.  The
@{b}Sold To@{ub} portion of the customer file is now completed.  Instead of typing
the same thing again for the @{b}Ship To@{ub} portion, click on each four of the
arrows pointing left that are next to the @{b}Ship To@{ub} fields.  This will copy
each line of information from the @{b}Ship To@{ub} fields to the@{b} Sold To@{ub} fields.  The
next field, @{b}Year To Date Customer Info - List Total@{ub}, will now be activated.
Enter "0.00", "0.00", and "0.00" for all three @{b}YTD Customer Info@{ub} fields.
This is a new customer, so they have not bought anything and they have not
gotten any discounts. Enter "Nobody" into the @{b}Contact@{ub} field and press
return.  Enter 1-555-555-5555 into the @{b}Phone #@{ub} and @{b}FAX #@{ub} fields and press
return.  Enter ".06" into all four tax rate fields.  Lastly, click on the
@{b}Blanket@{ub} Customer Type button, setting this customer to the highest standard
discounting.

@{b}Step 2@{ub}

Before exiting the @{i}Customer Editor@{ui}, the customer must be saved to disk.  To
do this, select @{b}Save As...@{ub} from the @{b}Customer@{ub} menu.  Press the save button
after you choose the Customer directory, and enter the filename as
"Test_Customer."  It is suggested that you keep all customer files in one
directory, such as the Customer directory.  The customer, now having been
saved to disk, is completed.  Click on the close button of the @{i}Customer
Editor@{ui}.  You will now be back at the main panel.



@{b}Step 3@{ub}

Now you need an inventory database.  Although an inventory database is not
required to use IMANDI Professional, it allows you to keep track of
inventory prices, numbers and sales.  Click on the @{b}Inventory@{ub} button on the
main panel.  The @{i}Inventory Editor@{ui} will now open.  To create a new item in
the current inventory database, press the @{b}Add@{ub} button at the bottom of the
window.  The @{b}Part Name@{ub} field will now be selected. Enter "Part 1" and press
return.  Next, enter "Description - Line 1" into the @{b}Description 1@{ub} field and
press return.  Press return through the next two fields, @{b}Description 2@{ub} and
@{b}Description 3@{ub}.  The @{b}Restock Editor@{ub} will now open its window on top of the
@{i}Inventory Editor@{ui} window. Click in the @{b}Date of Change@{ub} field, and press return
if the date is correct.  If the date is incorrect, your machine does not
have a battery backed up clock, and you will have to enter it manually.
Enter "1001" into the @{b}Purchase Order #@{ub} field and press return.  Enter "New
Item" into the @{b}Description@{ub} field and press return.  Enter "10" into the
@{b}Quantity Change@{ub} field, and again, press return.  A requester will appear
asking if all of the information you entered is correct.  Assuming it all
is, select the @{b}Yes@{ub} button.  Back in the @{i}Inventory Editor@{ui}, enter "1" into the
@{i}Recommended Quantity@{ui} field which is already selected and press return. Enter
"0" into the @{b}Quantity Sold@{ub} field and press return.  Enter "each" into the
@{b}Quantity Description@{ub} field and press return.  Enter "100.00" into the @{b}Cost@{ub}
field, and press return.  Enter "1000.00" into the Price field, and press
return.  Enter "Egad International" into the @{b}Supplier@{ub} field, and press
return.  Enter "5" into the @{b}Weight@{ub} field, press return, and press return two
more times to accept the current values in the @{b}Discount?@{ub} and @{b}Taxable?@{ub}
fields.  You have just created a one item inventory database.  Unlimited
entries may be made using the same procedure, but that's all we will enter
for now.

@{b}Step 4@{ub}

Like the customer file, we need to save the new inventory database that has
just been created.  Select @{b}Save As...@{ub} from the @{b}Inventory@{ub} menu. Press the
save button after you choose the Inventory directory, and enter the
filename, "Database_##-##-##" with ##-##-## being the current date. It is
suggested that you keep all inventory database files in one directory, such
as the Inventory directory.  It is also highly recommended that you should
save a database as a name, plus the current date, and continue to save the
current date every time that database is saved.  For example, today you
might save it as the name "Database_04-14-95", and tomorrow you would save
this same modified database as "Database_04-15-95."  This is a good practice
to follow should something happen to part of the disk or should the file
become corrupt.  The inventory database, now having been saved to disk, is
completed.  Click on the close button of the @{b}Inventory Editor@{ub}.  You will now
be back at the main panel.

@{b}Step 5@{ub}

Finally, it is time to create an invoice.  Press the@{b} New@{ub} button on the main
panel.  Four different windows will open.  Click in the @{i}Customer Editor@{ui}
window.  Select @{b}Open...@{ub} from the @{b}Customer@{ub} menu.  Select the file that you
saved earlier, "Test_Customer" in the Customer directory and press the @{b}OK@{ub}
button.  The customer file is now open, and will be used for this invoice.
Since we don't need to modify anything in the Customer Editor, press the@{b} F9@{ub}
key on your keyboard to shrink the window to getting it out of the way.

@{b}Step 6@{ub}

Now, click in the @{i}Header Editor@{ui} window in the @{b}Invoice #@{ub} field. Enter "1"
into this field, and press return.  Enter your initials into the @{b}Salesperson@{ub}
field, and press return.  The date should appear in the @{b}Date@{ub} field, so press
return.  If it does not appear, then enter the date manually, and press
return.  Enter "123" into the @{b}P.O. Number@{ub} field, and press return.  Enter
"123" into the @{b}Part Number@{ub} field and press return. Press return in the @{b}Date
Shipped@{ub} field to use the date currently entered there.  The @{i}Shipping
Requester@{ui} will now open up with your options of shippers.  Double-Click on
the USPS line to choose standard mail.  You will now be sent back to the
@{i}Header Editor@{ui}.  If the @{b}FOB@{ub} field is blank, enter your town and state,
separated by a comma and press return.  If the field already contains a town
and state, just leave it and press return. Press return in the @{b}Terms@{ub} field
to accept the current value.  The invoice header information is now
complete.  Using the window back button, send the @{i}Header Editor@{ui} to the back
of the screen.

@{b}Step 7@{ub}

Now, an inventory database must be opened.  Click in the @{i}Inventory Editor@{ui}
window and select @{b}Open...@{ub} from the @{b}Inventory@{ub} menu.  Select the database file
that you saved earlier, "Database_##-##-##" in the Inventory directory and
press the @{b}OK@{ub} button.  The database file is now open, and will be used for
this invoice.

@{b}Step 8@{ub}

The body of the invoice will now be created.  Click in the @{i}Invoice Editor@{ui}
window.  Select @{b}Parts@{ub} in the @{b}Mode@{ub} menu.  Enter "Part 1" into the @{b}Part Name@{ub}
field, and press return.  IMANDI Professional will now search the database
for the part name, and gather the information on that item. Press return in
the next three fields, @{b}Description 1@{ub}, @{b}Description 2@{ub}, and @{b}Description 3@{ub}.
Enter "1" into the @{b}Quantity@{ub} field, and press return.  The next few fields
will automatically be entered for you based on the information provided in
the inventory database, so press return through the @{b}Quantity Description,
Unit Price, Amount, Discount %,@{ub} and @{b}Discount $@{ub}. That one item has been
completed.  You want to add a small comment in the body of the invoice, so
select @{b}Babble@{ub} from the @{b}Mode@{ub} menu.  Press the space key, and press return to
enter a blank line.  Type "Thank you for this order." and press return. The
body of this invoice is finished.

@{b}Step 9@{ub}

It is time to print the invoice.  Turn on your printer if you have not
already done so, and set up the printer with an invoice form sheet to print
on.  Drag the @{i}Invoice Editor@{ui} window down from the top of the screen to
reveal the main panel.  On the main panel, click on the @{b}Print@{ub} button. The
@{i}Print Requester@{ui} will now open, and click in the @{b}Shipping@{ub} field.  Enter
"5.00" for $5.00 and press return.  Make sure only the form feed button is
checked, and press the @{b}Print@{ub} button if you are ready to print the invoice. A
requester providing the global invoice information will appear.  After you
have examined this requester, press the @{b}Thanks@{ub} button, and the invoice will
be printed.

@{b}Step 10@{ub}

The invoice is done, so now click on the @{i}Invoice Editor@{ui} window close button.
IMANDI Professional will ask to make sure you want to close the invoice.
Choose the @{b}Yes@{ub} button. A customer file save requester will appear.  Save the
customer file by pressing return to save it as the name that it was opened
as.  Next, an inventory database save requester will appear.  Save the
database.  You will now be back at the main panel, and are ready to start
another invoice.
@endnode

